---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProductGrid from '@/components/ProductGrid.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import SchemaOrg from '@/components/SchemaOrg.astro';
import CategoryNav from '@/components/CategoryNav.astro';
import CategoryGuides from '@/components/CategoryGuides.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import { buildCanonical } from '@/lib/seo';
import { itemListSchema } from '@/lib/schema';

const categorySlug = 'landscaping-outdoors';
const categoryLabel = 'Landscaping & Outdoors';

const products = await getCollection('products', ({ data }) => !data.draft && data.category === categorySlug);
products.sort((a, b) => b.data.addedDate.getTime() - a.data.addedDate.getTime());

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: categoryLabel, url: buildCanonical(`/${categorySlug}/`) },
];

const listSchema = itemListSchema(categoryLabel, products.map((p) => ({
  name: p.data.title,
  url: buildCanonical(`/${categorySlug}/${p.slug}/`),
})));
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Landscaping & Garden Products"
  description="Product information for paving, decking, fencing, drainage, and landscaping equipment. Independent specifications for landscapers, contractors, and homeowners."
>
  <SchemaOrg schema={listSchema} slot="head" />
  <div class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />

    <h1>Landscaping & Garden Products</h1>
    <p style="margin-bottom:2rem;color:var(--color-text-light);">
      Browse our range of {categoryLabel.toLowerCase()} products with full specifications, key features, and independent product information.
    </p>

    <div class="category-content">
      <h2>Landscaping & Outdoor Products for Trade and Domestic Use</h2>
      <p>
        Landscaping and outdoor construction encompasses some of the most varied work in the building trade —
        from hard landscaping (driveways, patios, retaining walls, drainage) through to soft landscaping
        (lawn preparation, planting, irrigation) and outdoor structures (decking, fencing, garden buildings).
        The products in this category must withstand the full range of UK weather conditions year-round, making
        material selection and specification particularly critical.
      </p>
      <p>
        Key product types include paving and block paving, natural stone, aggregates for drainage and bedding,
        decking (softwood, hardwood, and composite), fencing systems, garden walling, drainage and SUDS products,
        weed control membranes, outdoor power equipment, and irrigation systems.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Buying Considerations</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Frost resistance and slip resistance:</strong> External paving must be frost-resistant — look for
        products certified to BS EN 1339 (concrete flags) or BS EN 1341 (natural stone), and check the slip
        resistance rating. The UK Slip Resistance Group classifies surfaces from low to high slip risk;
        for steps and ramps, a minimum classification of moderate to high is required.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Timber treatment class:</strong> Timber used outdoors must be treated to a suitable Use Class
        under EN 335. UC3 covers above-ground outdoor use (decking, cladding, fencing above ground level);
        UC4 covers ground-contact and freshwater use (fence posts, sleepers). Using UC3 material in ground
        contact leads to rapid decay regardless of the quality of the timber itself.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Sustainable drainage:</strong> Since changes to planning guidance, new driveways and large
        paved areas often require sustainable drainage systems (SUDS) to manage surface water run-off and prevent
        increased flood risk. Permeable paving systems, soakaways, and attenuation crates must be sized for the
        catchment area and local rainfall intensity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Composite decking warranties:</strong> Composite decking products vary significantly in board density,
        core construction (hollow vs. solid), and surface texture. Warranties range from 10 to 25+ years; check
        whether the warranty covers fading, staining, and structural integrity separately, and what maintenance
        obligations apply to keep the warranty valid.
      </p>

      <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
      <p>
        Insufficient base preparation is the most common cause of landscaping failures. Block paving and patio
        flags that are not laid on a properly compacted, correctly graded sub-base and bed will rock, sink, and
        allow weeds through within a few seasons. The visible surface material often gets the blame, but the
        failure is almost always in the preparation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ignoring falls and drainage in patio design leads to pooling water against walls and structures,
        which causes damp issues over time. A minimum 1:60 fall away from buildings is standard practice.
      </p>

      <h2>Who Uses These Products?</h2>
      <p>
        Landscapers, groundworkers, garden designers, driveways contractors, local authority parks departments,
        and ambitious homeowners all need detailed specifications to select the right products and avoid costly
        errors. Clear technical information is particularly valuable for natural stone and composite products,
        where marketing claims can obscure important performance differences.
      </p>
    </div>

    <CategoryGuides categoryLabel={categoryLabel} />

    {products.length > 0 ? (
      <ProductGrid products={products.map((p) => ({
        title: p.data.title,
        slug: p.slug,
        category: p.data.category,
        brand: p.data.brand,
        shortDescription: p.data.shortDescription,
        featuredImage: p.data.featuredImage,
        affiliateUrl: p.data.affiliateUrl,
      }))} />
    ) : (
      <p>No products in this category yet. Check back soon.</p>
    )}
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
